The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 Stars amp; stones

 Sharmila Tagore with mother Ira Tagore at the Art Karat exhibition. Picture by Pabitra Das 

 What: 

 Inauguration of a jewellery exhibition by Art Karat.

 Where: Taj Bengal.

 When: Thursday afternoon.

 Take a look: The exhibition was inaugurated by actress Sharmila Tagore, looking elegant in a red and gold sari.

 The collection by designer Asha Kamal Modi draws inspiration from the Renaissance period of Rabindranath Tagore. An assortment of precious and semi-precious stones make up the collection. Necklaces, bangles, anklets, maangtikas and earrings with intricate patterns, filigree, wire and lattice work reflect an old world charm.

 The exhibition will be on at Genesis Art Gallery from March 17 to 23.

 Pocket Pinch: Prices start at Rs 1,500.

 Voiceover: Beautiful designs, wonderful use of colour and affordable prices make the line special, smiled Sharmila.




